ApplicationFees: The application fee for domestic applicants is $25 and for international applicants is $30.
TestPolicy: Undergraduate: "All entering degree-seeking students less than 21 years of age will be assessed initially for prescribed course placement according to valid ACT/SAT scores."
AdditionalInformation: For students who do not meet the criteria for guaranteed admission, a personal statement form will be required for review. International applicants are required to provide a copy of their passport photo page, a financial affidavit of support, and proof of English proficiency. Furthermore, individual graduate programs may have admission requirements that exceed those of the College of Graduate Studies, and prospective graduate students should consult the Graduate Catalog or their specific department for these requirements.
AdditionalDeadlines: ### Additional Deadlines at Middle Tennessee State University
GradScholarshipHigh: A Graduate Assistantship in the School of Music at Middle Tennessee State University is the highest graduate scholarship with an explicitly stated value, offering up to $21,066 per year for out-of-state students.
GradScholarshipLow: ## The lowest graduate scholarship explicitly stated for Middle Tennessee State University is $1,000.
